notesStmt.note: One leaf missing after folio 130 and 168 respectively.
First few leaves damaged, preserved on paper.

Folios 1r-2v, 186r-187vand contain Deuteronomy, chapters 13:7-18, 15:13-16:15, 30:20-31:10: Hebrew text with the sublinear punctuation, Targum with the simple superlinear puntuation, and Sa'adia Gaon's Arabic version in Hebrew characters. Has masorah magna and parva.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Midrash ha-gadol on Leviticus, attributed to David Adani.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 34; written lines: 34; Some marginal notes and additions. Hard-point ruling visible. Catchwords on every verso, partly preserved.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script of early 17th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Midrash Haggadol. Leviticus. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2215.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 13 December 1879, inscribed, folio [188v].
